Coronaviruses have a corrective exoribonuclease, the removal of which results in an extremely high rate of mutation and loss or even non-viability.
Interestingly, the nucleotide analogy of Remdesivere suppresses the replication of coronaviruses by inhibiting this exoribonuclease and RNA-dependent RNA polymerase.
Remdesivere is one of the most promising tools against SARS-COV-2, which needs to be tested in clinical trials.
