A stroke-air dryer, which releases 180 m/s (650 km/h, 400 miles/h), is capable of blowing micro-organisms out of his own unit and potentially infecting other users of the toilet and toilet within a radius of up to 2 metres.
The use of hand dryers with warm air spreads microorganisms within a radius of up to 0.25 metres from the dryer.
No significant microorganisms were detected using paper towels, and TUV Produkt und Umwelt conducted a study in 2005 to evaluate various methods of hand-drying.
