The addition of antiseptic chemicals to soap in hand-washing ("medical" or "antimicrobial" soap) helps to destroy bacteria.
Such anti-bacterial properties may be necessary before performing surgery or in a highly antibiotic resistant environment. The “cleaning” of hands before surgery requires a crane that can be turned on and off without touching it; a little chlor-hexidine or ion water should also be used to wash hands, sterile hand-washing towels, a sterile friction brush and another sterile instrument to clean under the fingernails.
